00:25.392 --> 00:27.593
[ PENCIL SCRATCHING ]

00:55.655 --> 00:57.623
[ PENCIL SCRATCHING ]

01:56.049 --> 01:57.983
[ FIRE CRACKLING ]

02:19.405 --> 02:21.373
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

02:40.527 --> 02:42.361
[ SIGHS ]

02:42.363 --> 02:43.996
COME ON, BUDDY.

02:43.998 --> 02:46.865
YOU DID THIS ONCE.
YOU CAN DO IT AGAIN.

02:52.872 --> 02:54.273
ALL RIGHT.

03:00.847 --> 03:02.848
[ TYPING ]

03:09.155 --> 03:11.256
[ CAR ENGINE APPROACHES ]

03:22.335 --> 03:23.702
HEY, BABE!

03:23.704 --> 03:25.470
HEY, PUNKIN PATCH!

03:25.472 --> 03:27.506
[ LAUGHS ]
HOW YOU DOING?

03:27.508 --> 03:29.241
LOOK AT YOU IN THAT DRESS

03:29.243 --> 03:31.476
AND THOSE SHOES
AND THAT FACE.

03:31.478 --> 03:33.045
MM.
COME HERE.

03:33.047 --> 03:34.046
COME HERE.

03:34.048 --> 03:35.414
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:35.416 --> 03:37.816
HOW'S THINGS GOING
AT THE, UH, BOUTIQUE?

03:37.818 --> 03:38.884
GOOD. WE, UH--

03:38.886 --> 03:40.586
I GOT THE MANNEQUINS IN TODAY.

03:40.588 --> 03:41.920
OH, YEAH?

03:41.922 --> 03:43.722
I'M STILL WAITING ON
THE DISPLAY TABLES,

03:43.724 --> 03:46.825
AND THE HANDYMAN NEEDS TO
FIX THE BATHROOMS.

03:46.827 --> 03:49.094
OH, YEAH,
SPEAKING OF HANDYMEN.

03:49.096 --> 03:50.762
YOU DIDN'T FIX
THE DOOR?

03:50.764 --> 03:52.164
I DIDN'T FIX
THE DOOR.

03:52.166 --> 03:54.766
WHAT, DO YOU TURN TO THE
RIGHT OR THE LEFT?

03:54.768 --> 03:55.934
KICK IT.

03:55.936 --> 03:58.136
YOU REALLY NEED
TO FIX THIS DOOR.

03:59.205 --> 04:01.373
[ GRUNTS ]
ATTAGIRL!

04:01.375 --> 04:03.275
SOON IT'S NOT
GONNA OPEN AT ALL.

04:03.277 --> 04:04.276
I GOT IT.

04:05.511 --> 04:07.446
HOW'D THE WRITING
GO TODAY?

04:08.615 --> 04:09.781
GOOD. GOOD, YEAH.

04:09.783 --> 04:11.516
UH, I THINK
I MADE A BREAKTHROUGH.

04:11.518 --> 04:14.353
GREAT.
I CAN'T WAIT TO READ IT.

04:21.094 --> 04:24.529
UM, WHOSE TURN IS IT
TO DO THE DISHES?

04:24.531 --> 04:26.031
I GOT 'EM.

04:26.033 --> 04:27.432
GOOD. [ CHUCKLES ]

04:27.434 --> 04:28.700
GONNA GET
SOME AFTERNOON SUN.

04:29.736 --> 04:30.669
OKAY.

04:36.209 --> 04:37.809
THAT'S A LOT
OF DISHES.

04:54.661 --> 04:55.994
[ LIGHTER FLICKS ]

05:30.263 --> 05:31.530
OH, SHIT.

05:31.532 --> 05:34.533
SORRY. I DIDN'T MEAN
TO INTERRUPT.

05:34.535 --> 05:36.835
I JUST WANTED TO TELL YOU
THAT I LOVE YOU.

05:36.837 --> 05:38.870
I LOVE YOU, TOO, BABY.

05:38.872 --> 05:41.139
ALL RIGHT. WELL, I DON'T
WANNA DISTRACT YOU.

05:41.141 --> 05:42.808
I'M GONNA GO GET READY.

05:42.810 --> 05:43.775
OKAY.

05:51.384 --> 05:53.151
WANNA JOIN ME?

05:53.153 --> 05:54.152
NOW?

05:54.154 --> 05:55.821
I JUST FINISHED
MY MAKEUP!

05:55.823 --> 05:57.456
YOU CAN DO IT AGAIN.

05:57.458 --> 05:58.523
IN 20 MINUTES?

05:59.892 --> 06:01.526
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.
YOU JUST DON'T WANNA

06:01.528 --> 06:03.829
SHARE THE SHOWER WITH ME BECAUSE
YOU'RE A WATER NAZI.

06:03.831 --> 06:05.664
[ CHUCKLES ] WELL, THAT'S TRUE.
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT?

06:05.666 --> 06:07.532
THEY ARE GONNA BE HERE
IN 20 MINUTES,

06:07.534 --> 06:08.967
SO YOU NEED TO HURRY UP.

06:08.969 --> 06:11.503
I'M A MAN.
I CAN BE READY IN FIVE.

06:11.505 --> 06:13.805
I'M SO GLAD WE'RE
HAVING PEOPLE OVER.

06:13.807 --> 06:16.742
I WAS BEGINNING TO FEEL LIKE WE
WERE BECOMING MY PARENTS.

06:18.711 --> 06:20.045
YOU THINK I'M YOUR DAD?

06:20.047 --> 06:22.214
THAT'S PRETTY CREEPY, BABE.

06:22.216 --> 06:24.082
OH, I MEAN,
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

06:24.084 --> 06:26.318
WE USED TO GO OUT WITH
COUPLES ALL THE TIME.

06:26.320 --> 06:27.919
NOW I'M SO BUSY
AT THE BOUTIQUE,

06:27.921 --> 06:29.721
AND YOU'RE CONSTANTLY IN
FRONT OF THE COMPUTER,

06:29.723 --> 06:31.723
AND AT NIGHT WE JUST
COME HOME AND COLLAPSE.

06:31.725 --> 06:32.724
YOU KNOW WHAT?

06:32.726 --> 06:34.159
LIFE IS GONNA
PASS US BY,

06:34.161 --> 06:35.827
AND ONE DAY
WE'RE GONNA WAKE UP

06:35.829 --> 06:37.129
AND REALIZE
THAT WE MISSED IT.

06:38.264 --> 06:39.998
SO TONIGHT,
LET'S JUST HAVE FUN.

06:42.034 --> 06:43.001
DEAL?

06:44.237 --> 06:46.405
NO TALK ABOUT WORK.

06:46.407 --> 06:47.672
NO.

06:47.674 --> 06:49.741
I CAN'T ARGUE WITH YOU
IN THAT DRESS.

06:52.412 --> 06:53.745
MM.

06:54.914 --> 06:56.548
YOU'LL MESS UP
MY MAKEUP.

06:56.550 --> 06:57.516
MM-HMM.

06:59.018 --> 07:01.119
SO I GOTTA ASK.
LIKE, WHOSE IDEA WAS THE BOWTIE?

07:01.121 --> 07:02.788
THE MATCHING?

07:02.790 --> 07:04.122
WHO DO YOU THINK?

07:04.124 --> 07:05.257
[ LAUGHTER ]

07:05.259 --> 07:07.726
I AM JUST SO AWFUL
TO THESE TWO.

07:07.728 --> 07:09.361
I DON'T KNOW HOW
THEY PUT UP WITH ME.

07:09.363 --> 07:10.929
IT'S TOTALLY FORGIVEN AS LONG
AS YOU DON'T HAVE

07:10.931 --> 07:12.030
THE MATCHING
CHRISTMAS PICTURES

07:12.032 --> 07:13.031
WITH EVERYONE
IN THE SAME COLOR.

07:13.033 --> 07:14.132
YOU KNOW
WHAT I MEAN?

07:14.134 --> 07:16.935
ACTUALLY, I WAS THINKING--
[ LAUGHS ]

07:16.937 --> 07:18.637
HOW DID YOU KNOW,
MICHAEL?

07:18.639 --> 07:20.439
REINDEER SWEATERS
FOR EVERYONE.

07:22.108 --> 07:23.575
SO A WHOLE YEAR?

07:23.577 --> 07:25.577
YEAH, A WHOLE YEAR.
NOT A DROP, MAN.

07:25.579 --> 07:26.611
NOT EVEN COUGH SYRUP.

07:26.613 --> 07:28.380
YEAH, AND, UH,
THAT IS NEXT.

07:28.382 --> 07:31.716
YES, IT IS. YES, IT IS.

07:31.718 --> 07:35.554
NOW YOU NEED TO LEARN TO EAT
LIKE A BIG BOY ALREADY,

07:35.556 --> 07:36.788
BECAUSE YOU ARE
A BIG BOY, MASON.

07:36.790 --> 07:37.889
OH, I'M SORRY, KAT.

07:37.891 --> 07:39.090
I'LL HELP YOU
CLEAN THIS UP.

07:39.092 --> 07:40.091
IT'S FINE.

07:40.093 --> 07:41.092
UM, SO, MICHAEL,

07:41.094 --> 07:42.661
TELL US ABOUT
THE NEW BOOK.

07:42.663 --> 07:43.829
WE'VE HEARD
SO MUCH ABOUT IT.

07:45.998 --> 07:48.433
I GOTTA TELL YOU,
IT'S KICKING MY BUTT,

07:48.435 --> 07:49.634
BUT I'M
TROUPING THROUGH.

07:49.636 --> 07:50.635
GOOD.

07:50.637 --> 07:52.737
WELL, I LOVE
"KNIGHT FIRE,"

07:52.739 --> 07:57.108
SO IF YOU EVER NEED ANYONE TO
GIVE THIS VERSION A READ,

07:57.110 --> 07:58.109
I'M YOUR WOMAN.

07:58.111 --> 07:59.845
YEAH, GOOD LUCK
WITH THAT.

07:59.847 --> 08:01.112
HE DOESN'T EVEN
LET ME READ IT.

08:01.114 --> 08:02.347
YEAH, TOP SECRET,
MM-HMM.

08:02.349 --> 08:05.417
NO WAY. IT WOULD
DRIVE ME ABSOLUTELY NUTS

08:05.419 --> 08:08.854
IF BILL WAS WORKING ON SOMETHING
THIS BIG AND KEPT IT FROM ME.

08:08.856 --> 08:10.689
WELL, I CAN'T WAIT
TILL IT'S READY.

08:10.691 --> 08:12.757
SHE MEANS IT.
SHE TELLS ALL HER FRIENDS

08:12.759 --> 08:14.759
SHE KNOWS THE GUY WHO WROTE
THAT "KNIGHT" BOOK.

08:14.761 --> 08:15.794
REALLY?
YEAH.

08:15.796 --> 08:17.262
AWW, THANK YOU.
YEAH.

08:17.264 --> 08:19.297
THEN SHE ASKS WHY
I CAN'T BE A WRITER, SO...

08:19.299 --> 08:20.799
YOU COULD BE
A WRITER, MAN.

08:20.801 --> 08:22.601
NO. I DON'T KNOW THE FIRST
THING ABOUT WRITING.

08:22.603 --> 08:24.703
I DIDN'T KNOW HOW TO WRITE A
BOOK UNTIL I WROTE A BOOK.

08:24.705 --> 08:26.538
I STILL DON'T KNOW
HOW TO WRITE A BOOK.

08:26.540 --> 08:28.006
MAKE IT UP
AS YOU GO ALONG.

08:28.008 --> 08:31.109
SO IS THIS NEW ONE A
CONTINUATION OF THE LAST ONE?

08:31.111 --> 08:32.644
KIND OF.
SAME MAIN CHARACTERS.

08:32.645 --> 08:34.212
OH, SO QUESTION
OF THE EVENING--

08:34.214 --> 08:35.847
IS THE KNIGHT
COMING BACK?

08:35.849 --> 08:37.883
THE KNIGHT IS
COMING BACK, YES. YES.

08:37.885 --> 08:40.118
YAY. HE MAKES IT SO MUCH FUN.
WHAT A GREAT CHARACTER.

08:40.120 --> 08:41.852
THANK YOU.
EVERYBODY LIKES THE KNIGHT.

08:41.855 --> 08:43.121
MICHAEL:
TOAST. TOAST.

08:43.123 --> 08:44.121
SOUNDS GOOD.

08:44.124 --> 08:45.123
TO FRIENDSHIP.

08:45.125 --> 08:46.091
TO FRIENDSHIP.
CHEERS.

08:48.494 --> 08:50.228
CHEERS.

08:50.230 --> 08:52.097
[ WATER RUNNING ]

09:06.178 --> 09:07.979
I'D MAKE A GREAT MOMMY.

09:11.017 --> 09:13.084
WOULDN'T OUR DAUGHTER
BE ADORABLE?

09:25.898 --> 09:27.899
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

09:28.901 --> 09:30.535
ARE YOU COMING TO BED?

09:30.537 --> 09:31.503
COMING.

10:12.979 --> 10:14.346
[ CLICK ]

10:24.991 --> 10:26.491
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

10:28.761 --> 10:29.728
I, UH--

10:31.130 --> 10:32.964
I THOUGHT
I HEARD SOMETHING.

10:32.966 --> 10:34.899
DID YOU SET THE ALARM?

10:34.901 --> 10:35.967
YEAH.

10:37.637 --> 10:39.938
GOD, THINKING OF
HEARING SOMETHING,

10:39.940 --> 10:41.606
I KEEP HAVING
THIS DREAM

10:41.608 --> 10:43.575
WHERE SOMETHING'S
WHISPERING IN MY EAR,

10:43.577 --> 10:45.310
AND I THINK
I UNDERSTAND 'EM.

10:45.312 --> 10:48.279
AND THEN I WAKE UP, AND I HAVE
NO IDEA WHAT THEY WERE SAYING.

10:48.281 --> 10:50.148
THAT'S ODD, HUH?

10:51.250 --> 10:52.651
YEAH, THAT'S WEIRD.

10:53.953 --> 10:55.587
WELL, I'M OFF TO BED.

10:55.589 --> 10:56.588
DON'T BE LONG.

10:56.590 --> 10:57.722
OKAY.

10:59.792 --> 11:01.760
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

11:14.507 --> 11:19.010
SO WHEN WILL YOU BE
FINISHED WITH YOUR BOOK?

11:20.012 --> 11:21.713
I DON'T KNOW, BABY.

11:21.715 --> 11:24.215
A MONTH JUST TO FINISH
THE FIRST DRAFT,

11:24.217 --> 11:25.984
AND THEN THERE'S
EDITOR'S NOTES

11:25.986 --> 11:28.887
AND PUBLISHER'S NOTES
AND NOTES NOTES AND...

11:30.890 --> 11:32.624
TAKES FOREVER
TO FINISH A BOOK.

11:32.626 --> 11:35.026
YEAH, TELL ME ABOUT IT.

11:35.028 --> 11:36.561
I WANNA BE STEPHEN KING.

11:36.563 --> 11:39.397
I WANNA WRITE,
LIKE, 12 A WEEK.

11:44.470 --> 11:45.704
THAT'S NICE.

11:45.706 --> 11:46.805
[ CHUCKLES ]

11:46.807 --> 11:48.807
DOES THAT FEEL GOOD?

11:51.043 --> 11:52.744
YEAH, THAT FEELS
REALLY GOOD.

11:52.746 --> 11:54.779
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

11:57.083 --> 11:58.550
COME HERE.

12:05.758 --> 12:07.092
YOU ARE SO BEAUTIFUL.

12:07.094 --> 12:08.259
YOU KNOW THAT?

12:08.261 --> 12:10.061
YOU ARE SO BEAUTIFUL.

12:15.167 --> 12:16.901
I WANNA FEEL YOU.

12:19.572 --> 12:21.906
I WANT YOU INSIDE ME.

12:27.246 --> 12:28.713
I WANNA HAVE YOUR BABY.

12:28.715 --> 12:31.850
WHAT? IS THAT
WHAT THIS IS ABOUT?

12:34.220 --> 12:35.954
CAN'T YOU SEE
THAT THAT'S WHAT I WANT?

12:35.956 --> 12:37.756
CAN WE NOT TALK
ABOUT THIS RIGHT NOW?

12:38.858 --> 12:40.692
WELL, WHEN CAN WE
TALK ABOUT IT?

12:40.694 --> 12:42.660
W-WE'VE TALKED ABOUT THIS
A HUNDRED TIMES.

12:43.963 --> 12:46.231
LOOK, I'M--
I'M ALMOST 37 YEARS OLD.

12:46.233 --> 12:47.465
I MEAN,
MOST OF MY FRIENDS

12:47.467 --> 12:50.268
ARE ON THEIR SECOND
OR THIRD KID BY NOW.

12:51.537 --> 12:54.105
I MEAN, EVERY SINGLE DAY
THAT WE WAIT

12:54.107 --> 12:57.642
IS ANOTHER DAY THAT WE DON'T GET
TO SPEND WITH OUR CHILD.

12:57.644 --> 12:59.377
LIKE, CAN'T WE JUST...

12:59.379 --> 13:01.045
HAVE A LITTLE FAITH
THAT--

13:01.047 --> 13:03.581
JUST LET ME
FINISH MY BOOK!

13:03.583 --> 13:05.750
THAT'S ALL, AND THEN WE
CAN TALK ABOUT FAMILY.

13:05.752 --> 13:09.053
THAT'S WHAT YOU SAID ABOUT ME
OPENING MY BOUTIQUE.

13:09.055 --> 13:09.954
NOW WHAT'S
THE REAL REASON?

13:09.956 --> 13:11.623
WHY ARE YOU
PULLING AWAY?

13:11.625 --> 13:13.558
THAT'S THE REAL REASON!
I-I'M UNDER PRESSURE!

13:13.560 --> 13:15.727
I WANT TO FINISH MY BOOK!
FUCK YOU!

13:15.729 --> 13:17.896
YOU KNOW WHAT THE REAL
FUCKING REASON IS!

13:17.898 --> 13:20.231
YEAH?
WHAT'S THE REAL REASON?

13:20.233 --> 13:22.467
YOU'RE NOT ATTRACTED TO ME!
WHAT DO YOU--

13:22.469 --> 13:24.235
YOU FUCKING WANT
SOME 18-YEAR-OLD?

13:24.237 --> 13:25.670
YOU WANT SOME FUCKING STUPID
FUCKING YOUNG CHICK?

13:25.672 --> 13:27.772
AM I TOO OLD FOR YOU?
WHAT? OH, MY GOD.

13:27.774 --> 13:29.641
BECAUSE THEN YOU COULD JUST WAIT
FOR 20 MORE YEARS!

13:29.643 --> 13:31.776
WHY CAN'T YOU JUST
GIVE ME WHAT I WANT?

13:31.778 --> 13:32.977
GOOD NIGHT.

13:32.979 --> 13:34.746
YOU KNOW,
I THOUGHT AFTER THREE YEARS,

13:34.748 --> 13:36.080
YOU WOULD HAVE
GROWN UP!

13:41.420 --> 13:43.421
[ TICKING ]

13:45.257 --> 13:47.225
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

13:49.595 --> 13:51.296
[ SNORING ]

13:51.298 --> 13:53.398
[ RING ]

13:54.633 --> 13:56.935
[ RING ]

13:56.937 --> 13:58.369
[ SNORING ]

13:58.371 --> 14:00.572
[ RING ]

14:01.807 --> 14:03.408
[ RING ]

14:04.610 --> 14:06.744
[ RING ]

14:13.185 --> 14:15.053
WEDNESDAY, 2:44 A.M.

14:15.055 --> 14:17.622
MAN: REMEMBER ME?

14:17.624 --> 14:19.557
[ CLICK, BEEP ]

14:19.559 --> 14:21.759
END OF MESSAGES.

14:33.873 --> 14:36.474
[ CLANKING ]

14:36.476 --> 14:38.476
[ ECHOING ]
HELLO, OLD CHAP.

14:38.478 --> 14:40.912
LONG TIME, NO SEE. HEH.

14:40.914 --> 14:43.481
I'VE MISSED
OUR TITTLE-TATTLES.

14:43.483 --> 14:45.049
AWW.

14:45.051 --> 14:47.385
TROUBLE WITH
THE MISSUS, EH?

14:47.387 --> 14:49.220
NOT TO WORRY.

14:49.222 --> 14:50.855
BELLY UP TO THE BAR, MATE.

14:50.857 --> 14:52.824
[ LAUGHING ]

14:55.527 --> 14:57.929
[ WILD LAUGHTER ]

15:00.499 --> 15:01.466
[ LAUGHTER FADES ]

15:29.695 --> 15:31.195
[ SNIFFS ]

15:39.138 --> 15:41.205
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

16:11.637 --> 16:14.472
CHEERS TO ONE YEAR OF
SOBRIETY AND MANY MORE.

16:14.474 --> 16:16.841
COULDN'T HAVE DONE IT
WITHOUT YOU, BABY.

16:18.510 --> 16:21.579
LOOK, I'M-- I'M REALLY SORRY
ABOUT THE OTHER NIGHT.

16:21.581 --> 16:23.848
IT'S JUST SEEING
BILL AND MARY'S SON--

16:23.850 --> 16:25.116
BABY, STOP.

16:25.118 --> 16:28.086
I WOULD PROBABLY BE DEAD
OR IN THE GUTTER

16:28.088 --> 16:30.154
IF YOU HADN'T
HAVE DRIED ME OUT,

16:30.156 --> 16:31.689
SO AS FAR
AS I'M CONCERNED,

16:31.691 --> 16:32.991
THERE ISN'T
AN 18-YEAR-OLD

16:32.993 --> 16:35.326
IN THE WORLD
THAT COULD TAKE YOUR PLACE.

16:35.328 --> 16:36.594
[ LAUGHS ]

16:36.596 --> 16:37.996
I LOVE YOU, BABY.

16:37.998 --> 16:39.330
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

16:39.332 --> 16:40.498
TO US.

16:43.969 --> 16:46.671
[ DISH SQUEAKING ]

16:49.274 --> 16:51.809
HEY, I WANTED
TO GIVE THIS TO YOU.

16:51.811 --> 16:54.879
IT'S A BIG-SHOT LITERARY AGENT
MY FRIEND TOLD ME ABOUT.

16:58.817 --> 17:00.485
MACMILLAN?

17:00.487 --> 17:03.054
BABY, THIS IS LIKE
A BIG SIX COMPANY.

17:03.056 --> 17:04.489
I MEAN,
"KNIGHT FIRE" DID OKAY,

17:04.491 --> 17:06.391
BUT IT WASN'T
A BEST SELLER. I'M NOT--

17:06.393 --> 17:08.126
I'M NOT READY FOR THIS.

17:08.127 --> 17:09.227
OHH. COME ON, BABE.

17:09.229 --> 17:10.694
DON'T BE SO HARD
ON YOURSELF.

17:10.696 --> 17:12.696
PEOPLE LOVE YOUR BOOK.

17:12.699 --> 17:16.034
AND AS HARD AS YOU'RE WORKING ON
THIS ONE, IT'S GONNA BE GREAT.

17:16.036 --> 17:18.970
SERIOUSLY,
STOP DOUBTING YOURSELF.

17:18.972 --> 17:20.972
YOU THINK?
YEAH.

17:20.973 --> 17:22.940
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

17:35.387 --> 17:36.788
[ WHISPERING ]
KATHERINE.

17:37.923 --> 17:39.657
KATHERINE.

17:44.430 --> 17:47.231
[ WIND RUSHING ]

17:47.233 --> 17:49.467
[ SIGHS ]
MICHAEL?

17:56.008 --> 17:58.076
[ NOISE QUIETS ]

17:58.078 --> 17:59.277
[ SIGHS ]

17:59.279 --> 18:01.813
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

18:03.082 --> 18:05.016
[ RING ]

18:06.552 --> 18:09.787
[ RING ]

18:09.789 --> 18:10.855
[ RING ]

18:10.857 --> 18:12.623
CAN YOU
GET THAT?

18:12.625 --> 18:15.026
[ RING ]

18:16.061 --> 18:18.763
[ RING ]

18:18.765 --> 18:21.099
[ RING ]

18:22.101 --> 18:24.135
[ RING ]

18:24.137 --> 18:25.703
HELLO.

18:28.040 --> 18:29.607
HELLO?

18:35.814 --> 18:38.149
[ RINGS ]

18:39.218 --> 18:40.885
[ RING ]

18:40.887 --> 18:42.787
YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT TIME IT IS?

18:42.789 --> 18:44.055
WOMAN:
REMEMBER ME?

18:45.290 --> 18:46.624
WHO IS THIS?

18:46.626 --> 18:48.793
REMEMBER ME?

18:48.795 --> 18:50.495
WHO IS THIS?

18:50.497 --> 18:52.497
[ CLICK, DIAL TONE ]

19:03.475 --> 19:04.876
[ SIGHS ]

19:07.179 --> 19:09.180
WHO WAS IT?

19:09.182 --> 19:10.748
WRONG NUMBER.

19:14.119 --> 19:15.453
MAN: REMEMBER ME?

19:15.455 --> 19:16.787
[ BEEP ]
END OF MESSAGES.

19:16.789 --> 19:18.356
ANY IDEA
WHO IT COULD BE?

19:18.358 --> 19:19.690
NO. SAME AS
THE OTHER NIGHT,

19:19.692 --> 19:21.125
BUT IT WAS
A WOMAN'S VOICE.

19:21.127 --> 19:22.360
IT'S WEIRD.

19:22.362 --> 19:24.629
YOU DON'T RECOGNIZE IT EITHER?
NOPE.

19:24.631 --> 19:27.198
AH, IT'S PROBABLY JUST
SOME KIDS FOOLING AROUND.

19:27.200 --> 19:29.000
WELL, HOPEFULLY
THEY'LL GET A LIFE.

19:29.002 --> 19:31.402
I HAVE A HARD ENOUGH TIME
SLEEPING AS IT IS.

19:32.804 --> 19:34.172
I LOVE YOU.

19:38.343 --> 19:39.343
HI, MITCH!

20:04.570 --> 20:06.504
I'M ONE YEAR SOBER
AS OF YESTERDAY.

20:06.506 --> 20:08.306
[ APPLAUSE ]

20:13.545 --> 20:16.080
IT'S ONE DAY AT A TIME, MAN.

20:18.483 --> 20:21.219
UM, ALCOHOL IS A DISEASE,

20:21.221 --> 20:25.223
AND I TRIED TO CONVINCE MYSELF
AND EVERYBODY ELSE

20:25.225 --> 20:29.694
THAT, UM, I COULD BEAT
THAT DISEASE ON MY OWN.

20:29.696 --> 20:32.997
AND I COULD FOR A LITTLE WHILE,
YOU KNOW,

20:32.999 --> 20:34.732
LIKE A DAY OR TWO.

20:34.734 --> 20:36.734
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:36.736 --> 20:37.835
[ SIGHS ]

20:37.837 --> 20:39.737
BUT IT TOOK
SOMEONE WHO LOVED ME

20:39.739 --> 20:42.773
MORE THAN I LOVED THE BOTTLE
TO SHAKE ME OUT OF IT,

20:42.775 --> 20:45.276
YOU KNOW, TO SHOW ME WHAT IT WAS
THAT I WAS THROWING AWAY,

20:45.278 --> 20:47.411
AND SHE SAVED MY LIFE,
BECAUSE SHE FORCED ME

20:47.413 --> 20:49.513
TO COME TO THESE MEETINGS,
OR SHE'D LEAVE ME.

20:51.250 --> 20:53.884
AND THIS IS SOMEONE
WHO STUCK BY ME

20:53.886 --> 20:55.753
AFTER I HAD A...

20:55.755 --> 20:58.689
DEBILITATING ACCIDENT
A WEEK AFTER I MET HER.

21:01.860 --> 21:05.029
I KNEW THAT IF MY DISEASE
WAS PUSHING HER AWAY,

21:05.031 --> 21:06.864
THEN I HAD TO DO SOMETHING,

21:06.866 --> 21:09.166
BECAUSE I COULD NOT
AFFORD TO LOSE HER.

21:11.303 --> 21:16.040
YOU DON'T HAVE TO HAVE
SOMEONE AT HOME TO SUCCEED,

21:16.042 --> 21:17.341
BUT, UM...

21:18.810 --> 21:20.478
IT SURE AS HELL HELPS.

21:24.716 --> 21:26.217
THAT'S ALL I GOT.

21:30.155 --> 21:32.657
WAS REALLY GOOD
TO SEE YOU TODAY, MIKE.

21:32.659 --> 21:33.924
A YEAR.

21:33.926 --> 21:35.926
BET IT'S LIKE
A CENTURY, HUH?

21:35.928 --> 21:37.628
YEAH, IT'S HAD ITS MOMENTS.

21:37.630 --> 21:40.498
JUST REMEMBER, EVERYBODY HERE
HAS BEEN WHERE YOU ARE,

21:40.500 --> 21:42.466
AND IF YOU
EVER NEED ANYTHING,

21:42.468 --> 21:44.702
YOU KNOW,
I'M HERE FOR YOU.

21:48.073 --> 21:49.140
HEY.

21:52.244 --> 21:54.779
YOU OKAY?
EVERYTHING OKAY?

21:54.781 --> 21:56.180
I, UH...

21:56.182 --> 21:58.983
I'M HAVING THOSE
HALLUCINATIONS AGAIN, MAN.

22:02.421 --> 22:03.454
DID YOU SLIP?

22:03.456 --> 22:04.455
OF COURSE NOT.

22:04.457 --> 22:05.790
OF COURSE NOT.

22:05.792 --> 22:07.458
MAN, LOOK, HERE'S THE THING.
UH-HUH.

22:07.460 --> 22:08.826
IT'S THE SAME THING
THAT USED TO HAPPEN

22:08.828 --> 22:10.461
WHEN I WAS DRINKING
AFTER THE ACCIDENT.

22:10.463 --> 22:11.929
ONLY NOW, THE SHIT'S
HAPPENING WHEN I'M SOBER.

22:11.931 --> 22:12.930
OKAY.

22:12.932 --> 22:14.598
I'M SCARED.

22:16.968 --> 22:19.603
OKAY, WHEN DID
THESE HALLUCINATIONS START?

22:19.605 --> 22:21.605
ABOUT FOUR DAYS AGO.

22:21.607 --> 22:22.940
ALL RIGHT.

22:22.942 --> 22:24.608
DID ANYTHING UNUSUAL
HAPPEN IN YOUR LIFE?

22:24.610 --> 22:26.143
IS ANYTHING
OVERWHELMING?

22:26.145 --> 22:28.479
YOU KNOW, SOME STRESS FROM OUT
OF NOWHERE, YOU KNOW?

22:28.481 --> 22:29.780
ANYTHING LIKE THAT?

22:29.782 --> 22:31.482
NO, MAN, IT'S THE
SAME AS ALWAYS.

22:31.484 --> 22:32.550
KATHERINE WANTS
TO HAVE A BABY.

22:32.552 --> 22:33.884
I CAN'T FINISH
THE NOVEL.

22:33.886 --> 22:36.020
HOW'S THE BOOK COMING?

22:36.022 --> 22:37.455
IT'S FUCKING BRUTAL.

22:37.457 --> 22:38.889
I KEEP WAITING
FOR INSPIRATION

22:38.891 --> 22:40.291
TO COME,
SHOW ME WHAT TO DO,

22:40.293 --> 22:42.893
AND IT
JUST WON'T COME.

22:42.895 --> 22:46.197
WELL, LOOK.
JUST BE OPEN TO IT,

22:46.199 --> 22:48.032
AND IT WILL, OKAY?

22:48.034 --> 22:50.201
IT WILL COME.
[ SIGHS ]

22:52.704 --> 22:54.638
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

22:56.007 --> 22:57.541
[ RING ]
JESUS, MICHAEL!

22:57.543 --> 22:58.843
PLEASE
DO SOMETHING!

22:58.845 --> 23:01.145
[ RING ]

23:02.180 --> 23:04.148
[ RING ]

23:05.183 --> 23:07.718
[ RING ]

23:07.720 --> 23:08.886
LOOK,
YOU SON OF A BITCH--

23:08.888 --> 23:10.121
GIRL: REMEMBER ME?

23:12.057 --> 23:13.057
WHO IS THIS?

23:13.059 --> 23:14.058
REMEMBER ME?

23:14.060 --> 23:15.092
WHO IS THIS?

23:15.094 --> 23:16.160
WHERE ARE
YOUR PARENTS?

23:16.162 --> 23:17.161
REMEMBER ME?

23:17.163 --> 23:18.362
WHERE ARE YOUR PARENTS?

23:18.364 --> 23:19.530
I'M GONNA CALL
THE FUCK--

23:19.532 --> 23:20.531
[ CLICK, DIAL TONE ]

23:20.533 --> 23:22.833
GOD DAMN IT!

23:54.599 --> 23:56.066
[ GASPS ] DON'T DO THAT!
DO WHAT?

23:56.068 --> 23:57.601
DON'T JUMP OUT
AT ME LIKE THAT!

23:57.603 --> 23:59.103
I'M SO SORRY!
I HEARD YOU YELLING--

23:59.105 --> 24:00.571
THERE WAS THIS KID'S
VOICE ON THE PHONE!

24:00.573 --> 24:01.238
WHAT?
LOOK AT THE FRIDGE!

24:01.240 --> 24:02.640
LOOK AT WHAT?

24:04.609 --> 24:06.377
NOTHING.

24:06.379 --> 24:07.611
ARE YOU OKAY?
NO.

24:08.880 --> 24:10.481
NO, I'M NOT.

24:10.483 --> 24:11.749
UM...

24:11.751 --> 24:13.484
WHO DO WE KNOW
WITH A DAUGHTER?

24:13.486 --> 24:14.552
WHO'S GOT KIDS?

24:14.554 --> 24:15.553
WHO'S GOT KIDS, BABY?

24:15.555 --> 24:16.620
WHO'S GOT KIDS?!

24:16.622 --> 24:18.189
I KNOW A LOT OF PEOPLE
WITH KIDS.

24:19.424 --> 24:21.892
I'M GOING BACK TO BED.

24:21.894 --> 24:23.861
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

24:33.405 --> 24:34.972
[ HOUSE ALARM BLARING ]

24:34.974 --> 24:36.073
SOMEBODY'S HERE.
SOMEBODY'S IN THE HOUSE.

24:36.075 --> 24:37.875
SHH. SHH.

24:45.617 --> 24:46.617
STAY.

24:46.619 --> 24:47.751
NO, I'M COMING WITH YOU.

24:49.120 --> 24:50.421
STAY CLOSE.

24:56.361 --> 24:58.362
[ BLARING CONTINUES ]

25:14.212 --> 25:15.513
[ BLARING STOPS ]

25:18.316 --> 25:20.184
I HAVE A WEAPON!

25:23.288 --> 25:25.222
I'M SORRY.
SHH.

25:30.195 --> 25:32.196
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

25:47.512 --> 25:49.480
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

25:54.052 --> 25:56.053
WELL?

25:56.055 --> 25:57.922
I CHECKED
ALL AROUND YOUR HOUSE,

25:57.924 --> 26:00.324
AND THERE'S NO SIGN
OF A FORCED ENTRY.

26:00.326 --> 26:02.359
MAYBE IT WAS A RACCOON

26:02.361 --> 26:04.995
OR SOME OTHER VARMINT
TRIGGERED THE ALARM.

26:04.997 --> 26:06.196
IT'S PRETTY COMMON
IN THESE PARTS.

26:06.198 --> 26:07.565
TH-THAT HAPPENS?

26:07.567 --> 26:09.266
NO. NO, WE'VE BEEN HERE
FOR THREE YEARS.

26:09.268 --> 26:11.001
IT'S NEVER HAPPENED.

26:11.003 --> 26:12.937
MAYBE SOMEONE GOT DRUNK

26:12.939 --> 26:16.574
AND SET OFF THE SYSTEM
STUMBLING AROUND IN THE DARK.

26:16.576 --> 26:18.075
[ CHUCKLES ]
REALLY?

26:18.077 --> 26:20.444
I'VE BEEN SOBER FOR A YEAR,
SHERIFF, SO--

26:20.446 --> 26:22.513
I'VE SEEN PEOPLE
SOBER 30 YEARS,

26:22.515 --> 26:26.116
THEN SLIP RIGHT BACK INTO OLD
HABITS WITHOUT MISSING A DAY.

26:26.118 --> 26:27.384
H-HE DOESN'T DRINK.

26:27.386 --> 26:29.186
I'VE BEEN
TAKING CARE OF HIM.

26:29.188 --> 26:31.422
WELL, ISN'T MR.
LANE A LUCKY MAN TO HAVE

26:31.424 --> 26:32.623
YOU WATCH HIS BACK?

26:32.625 --> 26:34.592
HEY, YOU KNOW,
WHILE YOU'RE HERE,

26:34.594 --> 26:36.293
WE'VE BEEN GETTING THESE
REALLY WEIRD PHONE CALLS

26:36.295 --> 26:37.695
AT ALL HOURS
OF THE NIGHT.

26:37.697 --> 26:39.463
IS THERE ANYTHING
YOU CAN DO ABOUT THAT?

26:39.465 --> 26:41.865
IT'S PROBABLY JUST KIDS
MAKING PRANK CALLS.

26:41.867 --> 26:43.133
MICHAEL:
NO, IT'S NOT.

26:43.135 --> 26:44.234
IT'S DIFFERENT
PEOPLE.

26:44.236 --> 26:46.070
ONE OF THEM WAS
A YOUNG CHILD.

26:46.072 --> 26:48.072
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

26:48.074 --> 26:51.075
YEAH, THAT'S THE BURGLARY
ON SHERWOOD. FALSE ALARM.

26:51.077 --> 26:53.077
DEPUTY'S GOING FOR A COFFEE RUN.
DID YOU WANT--

26:53.079 --> 26:55.879
WHY DON'T YOU TELL THE DEPUTY TO
STAY PUT TILL I GET BACK?

26:55.881 --> 26:57.381
COPY THAT.

26:58.416 --> 27:00.718
SO? YOU GONNA
DO ANYTHING?

27:00.720 --> 27:01.719
ABOUT WHAT?

27:01.721 --> 27:02.953
NOBODY BROKE IN.

27:02.955 --> 27:04.655
YOU'RE GETTING
PRANK CALLS FROM KIDS.

27:04.657 --> 27:06.090
CHECK WITH
YOUR NEIGHBORS.

27:06.092 --> 27:07.725
I'M SURE THEY'RE GETTING
THE SAME CALLS.

27:07.727 --> 27:09.393
WE HAVE A SMALL DEPARTMENT
HERE, SIR.

27:09.395 --> 27:13.263
I LIKE TO LIMIT
THE UNNECESSARY PAPERWORK.

27:13.265 --> 27:15.799
NOW SHOULD
AN ACTUAL PERSON BREAK IN,

27:15.801 --> 27:17.101
DON'T HESITATE TO CALL.

27:17.103 --> 27:18.102
HAVE A GOOD EVENING.

27:18.104 --> 27:19.136
YES, SIR.
YOU, TOO.

27:19.138 --> 27:20.137
THANKS.

27:20.139 --> 27:21.705
ASSHOLE.
SHH.

27:27.345 --> 27:28.879
WHEW.

27:32.617 --> 27:34.318
MITCH, RIGHT?

27:35.353 --> 27:37.154
I'M MICHAEL,
YOUR NEIGHBOR.

27:37.156 --> 27:38.622
HI, MICHAEL,
MY NEIGHBOR.

27:38.624 --> 27:41.125
GOOD TO MEET YOU
AFTER THREE YEARS.

27:41.127 --> 27:43.460
YEAH, I DON'T GET OUT MUCH.

27:43.462 --> 27:45.162
I WORK FROM HOME,
YOU KNOW.

27:45.164 --> 27:46.263
IT'S COOL, DUDE.

27:46.265 --> 27:47.665
WHAT'S UP?

27:47.667 --> 27:50.167
UM, LOOK, HAVE YOU, UH--

27:50.169 --> 27:53.604
HAVE YOU BEEN GETTING ANY CALLS,
LIKE IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT?

27:53.606 --> 27:55.673
PEOPLE KEEP CALLING US
AND SAYING, "REMEMBER ME,"

27:55.675 --> 27:57.941
AND THEN JUST HANGING UP.
DOES THAT SOUND FAMILIAR?

27:57.943 --> 27:59.777
HOLY SHIT.

27:59.779 --> 28:01.111
YOU GET THOSE, TOO?

28:02.480 --> 28:04.014
SO WHAT IS IT,

28:04.016 --> 28:05.349
JUST SOMEONE
MESSING AROUND?

28:05.351 --> 28:07.117
YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHO IT IS?

28:07.119 --> 28:09.820
YEAH, IT'S USUALLY
ONE OF MY THREE EX-WIVES

28:09.822 --> 28:12.222
BITCHING THAT I'M LATE
WITH THE ALIMONY.

28:12.224 --> 28:15.359
[ LAUGHING ]

28:15.361 --> 28:17.027
REAL FUCKING FUNNY.
COME ON.

28:17.029 --> 28:18.829
I'M SORRY, MAN.
COME ON. HAVE A BEER.

28:18.831 --> 28:20.531
COME ON, ALIMONY!

28:20.533 --> 28:22.633
THAT'S FUNNY!
COME ON! HEH!

28:31.476 --> 28:33.444
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

28:38.750 --> 28:41.118
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

28:44.889 --> 28:45.889
HELLO.

28:45.891 --> 28:48.759
HEY, ARE YOU OKAY?

28:48.761 --> 28:50.494
HEY, BABY, YEAH.

28:50.496 --> 28:52.329
EVERYTHING'S GREAT.
HOW'S YOUR DAY?

28:53.431 --> 28:54.732
YOU'RE NOT DRINKING,
ARE YOU?

28:55.767 --> 28:57.067
WHAT?

28:57.069 --> 28:58.936
WHY WOULD
YOU EVEN SAY THAT?

28:58.938 --> 29:01.505
IT'S JUST MARY
CALLED ME TODAY.

29:01.507 --> 29:03.173
SHE'S FRIENDS
WITH MITCH'S GIRLFRIEND,

29:03.175 --> 29:05.709
AND APPARENTLY MITCH THOUGHT YOU
WERE ACTING WEIRD.

29:05.711 --> 29:08.378
ALL I DID IS GO OVER THERE
AND ASK THE GUY

29:08.380 --> 29:09.646
IF HE'S GETTING THE SAME PHONE
CALLS WE ARE.

29:09.648 --> 29:10.380
THAT'S IT.

29:10.382 --> 29:11.582
THAT'S ALL?
THAT'S ALL.

29:11.584 --> 29:13.684
YOU KNOW, HE WAS A BIT
OF A DICK ABOUT IT,

29:13.686 --> 29:15.085
AND NOW APPARENTLY
HE'S TELLING THE WHOLE TOWN.

29:15.087 --> 29:17.121
LOOK, IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

29:17.123 --> 29:18.555
REMEMBER WHAT
THE SHERIFF SAID?

29:18.557 --> 29:20.524
PROBABLY A LOT OF PEOPLE
ARE GETTING THE CALLS.

29:20.526 --> 29:22.893
YEAH, BUT I'M THE ONLY ONE WHO'S
A DRUNK FOR CHECKING IN ON IT.

29:22.895 --> 29:24.228
THAT'S NOT TRUE!

29:24.230 --> 29:26.063
MICHAEL, A-ARE YOU
SURE YOU'RE--

29:26.065 --> 29:27.765
KNOW WHAT? I GOTTA GO.

29:31.870 --> 29:33.837
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

29:40.712 --> 29:42.146
SON OF A BITCH.

30:07.138 --> 30:08.605
[ CLANKING ]

30:08.607 --> 30:10.574
KNIGHT:
WHAT SHITE.

30:10.576 --> 30:12.442
GET OUT OF HERE.

30:12.444 --> 30:14.011
THIS ISN'T YOU.

30:14.013 --> 30:16.046
YOU'RE WASTING YOUR TIME.

30:17.348 --> 30:19.483
LEAVE ME ALONE.

30:19.485 --> 30:22.252
YOU HAVE BIGGER THINGS
AHEAD OF YOU.

30:23.288 --> 30:25.088
YOU ARE A VISIONARY.

30:25.090 --> 30:27.157
I'M HALLUCINATING.

30:27.159 --> 30:31.495
ALL YOU NEED IS
A LIFT OF INSPIRATION.

30:31.497 --> 30:32.629
LEAVE ME ALONE!

30:32.631 --> 30:33.664
[ OBJECT CLATTERS ]

30:34.933 --> 30:36.733
[ YAWNS ]

30:38.269 --> 30:41.505
YOU WERE NEVER LIKE THIS
BEFORE KATHERINE CAME ALONG.

30:41.507 --> 30:43.774
I THINK SHE'S DRIVING YOU
TO THE LOONY BIN.

30:43.776 --> 30:46.276
LEAVE ME ALONE!

30:46.278 --> 30:47.644
DON'T WORRY.

30:47.646 --> 30:49.346
I'LL BRING YOU BACK.

30:49.348 --> 30:51.248
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

30:53.518 --> 30:55.152
BABY, I'M SO SORRY.
IT'S--

30:55.154 --> 30:56.520
WOMAN: REMEMBER ME?

30:56.522 --> 30:58.055
WHO THE HELL IS THIS?

30:58.057 --> 30:59.590
REMEMBER ME?

31:01.159 --> 31:02.626
IF YOU DON'T
STOP CALLING ME--

31:02.628 --> 31:05.362
[ SCREAMING ]

31:05.364 --> 31:07.364
IF YOU DON'T
STOP CALLING ME--

31:07.366 --> 31:09.132
[ DIAL TONE ]

31:09.134 --> 31:11.268
[ TELEPHONE SHATTERS ]

31:19.744 --> 31:21.278
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

31:23.882 --> 31:25.916
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

31:32.323 --> 31:34.725
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

31:40.231 --> 31:41.999
HEY, MAN, UH,

31:42.001 --> 31:43.233
SORRY ABOUT
JOKING AROUND EARLIER.

31:43.235 --> 31:45.402
IT WAS, LIKE,
SO UNCOOL OF ME. I--

31:45.404 --> 31:47.704
MITCH, I NEED YOU
TO DO TWO THINGS.

31:47.706 --> 31:51.441
ONE, NEVER, EVER LOOK
AT MY WIFE AGAIN,

31:51.443 --> 31:54.278
AND TWO, GET OFF MY PORCH
IN THE NEXT FIVE SECONDS.

31:54.280 --> 31:56.580
AND IF ANYONE HEARS ABOUT THIS
CONVERSATION AROUND TOWN,

31:56.582 --> 31:58.749
YOU SHOULD KNOW
I HAVE A .357.

31:58.751 --> 32:00.083
YOU'RE SERIOUSLY
THREATENING ME?

32:00.085 --> 32:02.452
STAY ON MY PORCH,
AND FIND OUT.

32:02.454 --> 32:03.487
COOL.

32:10.295 --> 32:13.630
I TALKED WITH ARIEL,
MITCH'S GIRLFRIEND?

32:13.632 --> 32:15.866
SHE SAYS THAT YOU
THREATENED TO SHOOT HIM.

32:15.868 --> 32:17.567
I TOLD HIM TO MIND
HIS OWN BUSINESS.

32:17.569 --> 32:18.902
SO YOU THREATENED
TO SHOOT HIM?

32:18.904 --> 32:21.104
I MENTIONED AS AN ASIDE
THAT I HAVE A GUN.

32:21.106 --> 32:23.240
HOW HE CHOSE TO INTERPRET IT
IS HIS BUSINESS.

32:23.242 --> 32:25.309
WHAT THE HELL IS WRONG
WITH YOU LATELY?

32:25.311 --> 32:27.377
HE CALLED ME A DRUNK, KAT.
[ GRUNTS ]

32:27.379 --> 32:29.079
WELL, HE SHOULDN'T
HAVE SAID THAT,

32:29.081 --> 32:31.648
BUT, YOU KNOW, MAYBE HE WAS JUST
WORRIED ABOUT YOU.

32:31.650 --> 32:34.084
MAYBE IF YOU GOT TO KNOW
SOME OF THESE PEOPLE,

32:34.086 --> 32:36.286
THEY'D BE ABLE TO TELL
WHO YOU REALLY ARE.

32:36.288 --> 32:38.255
I JUST FEEL
LIKE A STRANGER HERE,

32:38.257 --> 32:39.656
AND--AND I
REALLY LIKE IT HERE,

32:39.658 --> 32:41.992
AND I WANT TO GET
TO KNOW THESE PEOPLE,

32:41.994 --> 32:43.393
A-AND YOU'RE
THREATENING THEM?

32:43.395 --> 32:45.295
I MEAN, DO YOU REALLY
THINK THAT THAT HELPS?

32:45.297 --> 32:46.363
DO YOU THINK THIS HELPS?!

32:47.632 --> 32:49.833
DO YOU THINK I NEED
ANY MORE PRESSURE?

32:49.835 --> 32:51.835
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

33:04.849 --> 33:07.484
KATHY, COULD YOU GET ME
THE FLATHEAD, BABE?

33:07.486 --> 33:09.853
[ HUMMING ]

33:14.459 --> 33:15.625
HEY, KATHY!

33:15.627 --> 33:17.427
COULD YOU GET ME
THE FLATHEAD, PLEASE?

33:17.429 --> 33:19.463
[ CONTINUES HUMMING ]

33:19.465 --> 33:21.298
WHAT, ARE YOU GIVING ME
THE SILENT TREATMENT?

33:21.300 --> 33:23.166
COULD YOU PLEASE
GET ME THE FLATHEAD?

33:23.168 --> 33:24.768
WHAT ARE YOU
SHOUTING ABOUT?

33:29.707 --> 33:31.708
[ HUMMING ]

33:33.044 --> 33:34.711
NEVER MIND.

33:38.049 --> 33:39.783
WHAT?
DID YOU SEE HER?

33:39.785 --> 33:41.184
WHO?
THE WOMAN.

33:41.186 --> 33:43.020
KATHERINE:
WHAT WOMAN?

33:45.289 --> 33:46.957
THE WOMAN IN THE DRESS.

33:53.531 --> 33:55.565
I DIDN'T SEE ANYONE.

33:55.567 --> 33:57.567
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

34:09.714 --> 34:11.982
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

34:11.984 --> 34:14.016
LOOK, I JUST
WANT YOU TO ADMIT

34:14.018 --> 34:16.018
THAT YOU HAVEN'T REALLY
BEEN YOURSELF LATELY,

34:16.021 --> 34:18.255
AND WE CAN
FIGURE IT OUT FROM THERE.

34:23.728 --> 34:26.596
[ WATER RUNNING ]

34:26.598 --> 34:29.498
AND I THINK YOU SHOULD
APOLOGIZE TO MITCH!

34:31.235 --> 34:33.235
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

34:56.928 --> 34:58.728
HOW'D IT GO?
I MEAN...

34:58.730 --> 35:00.197
I'M NOT GONNA
GET INVITED

35:00.199 --> 35:01.598
TO POKER NIGHT,
BUT WENT OKAY.

35:03.101 --> 35:05.535
THANK YOU.

35:05.537 --> 35:06.870
YEAH.

35:06.872 --> 35:09.539
YOU, UH--YOU WANT
TO CALL BILL AND MARY,

35:09.541 --> 35:12.109
HAVE THEM BRING MASON
AGAIN OVER TOMORROW?

35:12.111 --> 35:14.077
